%% Diagram: Spanner commit wait turns clock uncertainty into external consistency
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant TT as TrueTime
    participant Co as Coordinator
    participant P as Participants
    participant Cl as Reader

    Co->>P: prepare, collect prepare timestamps
    P-->>Co: prepare ts (per participant)

    Co->>TT: TT.now() returns earliest, latest
    Co->>Co: pick s = max(latest, max(prepare ts), prev commit + 1)

    rect rgb(255, 244, 220)
    note over Co,TT: Commit wait\nblock until TT.now().earliest > s\n(typically 1 to 7 ms in Google production,\ndocs cap at under 10 ms)
    Co->>TT: TT.now()
    TT-->>Co: still earliest <= s
    Co->>TT: TT.now() (after wait)
    TT-->>Co: earliest > s
    end

    Co->>P: COMMIT at timestamp s
    Co-->>Cl: visible

    note over Cl: Any later transaction T'\nstarting after now in real time\nmust get a timestamp > s.\nReal-time order is preserved\n=> external consistency.
